        "content": "As of 2026, Tokyo's population varies depending on the area considered:\n\n- **Tokyo Metropolis (Tokyo Prefecture):** Approximately 14.2 million residents. ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Demographics_of_Tokyo?utm_source=openai))\n\n- **Tokyo Metropolitan Area (including neighboring prefectures):** Around 33.4 million people. ([nippon.com](https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-data/h02639/?utm_source=openai))\n\n- **Greater Tokyo Area:** Approximately 37 million residents. ([macrotrends.net](https://www.macrotrends.net/global-metrics/cities/21671/tokyo/population?utm_source=openai))\n\nThese figures reflect Tokyo's status as one of the world's largest urban areas, though its population has been experiencing a gradual decline in recent years. ",
